name: Congressional Medal of Honor Foundation
tweet: The iconic image, captured by Associated Press photographer Joe Rosenthal, of six Marines raising the second American flag at Iwo Jima occurred on February 23, 1945, signifying the conclusion of the American campaign in the Pacific during World War II.

name: Congressional Medal of Honor Foundation
tweet:
The epic battle produced 27 Medal of Honor Recipients. The Marine Corps War Memorial (Iwo Jima Memorial) was dedicated on November 10, 1954. The U.S. Navy also commissioned two ships with the name USS Iwo Jima (LPH-2) and USS Iwo Jima (LHD-7).

Lest We Forget!
